А    Magnitude, a measure of the brightness of a star - the Ancient  Greek    А
А    astronomers divided  the stars  into six  magnitudes. First-magnitude    А
А    stars  were  the  brightest,  and  sixth-magnitude  stars  were   the    А
А    faintest. This system has been kept in modern times, when the new era    А
А    of MAGNiTUDE has started.                                                А
А                                                                             А
А    If you  feel like  you have  the power  to face first-magnitude stars    А
А    contact us at:                                                           А
А    team.magnitude@gmail.com or Maybe on IRC.                                А
